Bundled Python wheel cohort (~47 packages)
Mixed permissive licenses (MIT, BSD, Apache-2.0, PSF).

Alongside `adeu`, the `.deb` bundles approximately 47 transitive Python
wheels at `ui/desktop/src/resources/python/wheels/` (e.g., `aiofile`,
`authlib`, `beartype`, `cffi`, `cryptography`, `diff_match_patch`,
`httpx`). Each wheel's `dist-info/` directory carries its own LICENSE
and METADATA; per-wheel attribution travels with the wheel and is
extracted at install time into the bundled CPython runtime.

No copyleft-licensed wheels are knowingly bundled. If a future bundling
pass introduces a wheel under copyleft terms, surface the conflict and
either replace, vendor as a separate optional component, or add explicit
acknowledgment here.

