Rust transitive dependencies

The full Rust dependency list for the goose runtime is in `Cargo.lock`
at the repo root. All Rust dependencies are permissive (Apache-2.0, MIT,
BSD, or dual-licensed combinations). Three Cargo `[patch]` entries pin
git-tracked forks for ongoing upstream work — see `Cargo.toml`:

  - `v8` (the V8 JavaScript engine Rust wrapper) — points at the local
    `vendor/v8/` wrapper, which depends on `v8-goose` from crates.io
    (Apache-2.0).
  - `cudaforge` (https://github.com/jbg/cudaforge) — git pin, license to
    be confirmed by maintainer at next pass; surface to the user whether
    Oscar GC actually invokes any GPU code path (if not, the patch can
    be removed entirely).
  - Five `opentelemetry-*` packages — git pins to a specific
    opentelemetry-rust commit (Apache-2.0), temporary per the `TODO`
    comment in `Cargo.toml` ("switch to released version in
    opentelemetry 0.32.0").

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Node / Electron transitive dependencies

The full Node dependency list for the desktop app is in
`ui/desktop/pnpm-lock.yaml`. All direct dependencies are permissive:
Electron (MIT), React (MIT), Radix UI (MIT), Tailwind CSS (MIT),
framer-motion (MIT), zod (MIT), react-markdown (MIT), lucide-react
(ISC), `@mcp-ui/client` (MIT), `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` (MIT),
`@modelcontextprotocol/ext-apps` (MIT). No copyleft-licensed npm
dependencies are knowingly bundled.

